<!--template match = subSubSection[ancestor::treatment]--><tp:treatment-sec sec-type="discussion">
<!--template match = paragraph--><p>
Remarks
. 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>Konowia megapolitana</tp:taxon-name>
is a small species, characterized by the fairly smooth and sparsely punctate vertex (
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-9--151-250-1649-1673-">Fig. 3H, K</xref>
), the very thin antenna (
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-12--151-250-1789-1813-">Fig. 4P, Q</xref>
), the entirely distinctly microsculptured and mat mesoscutellum, and the short valvula 3 (apical sheath) (
<!--template match = figureCitation--><xref rid="fig-17--151-250-1262-1286-">Fig. 8D</xref>
) (see the key for more details). The male is unknown. 
<!--template match = bibRefCitation--><xref rid="ref15223">Enslin (1918)</xref>
referred to the males of 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>K megapolitana</tp:taxon-name>
but we agree with 
<!--template match = bibRefCitation--><xref rid="ref15347">Jansen (1987)</xref>
to regard them as males of 
<!--template match = taxonomicName--><tp:taxon-name>K. betulae</tp:taxon-name>
.
</p>
<!--template match = paragraph--><p>
We were not able to find any published collection records of this species from the Far East, though 
<!--template match = bibRefCitation--><xref rid="ref17377">Zhelochovtsev &amp; Zinovjev (1996)</xref>
listed the Southern Far East and 
<!--template match = bibRefCitation--><xref rid="ref15498">Lelej &amp; Taeger (2007)</xref>
listed 
Primorskij kraj
in the distribution of this species.
</p>
